==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Widen
<hw>Wid"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Widened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Widening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make wide or wider; to extend
in breadth; to increase the width of; <as>as, to <ex>widen</ex> a field;
to <ex>widen</ex> a breach; to <ex>widen</ex> a stocking.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Widen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Widen
<hw>Wid"en</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To grow wide or wider; to
enlarge; to spread; to extend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Arches <qex>widen</qex>, and long aisles extend.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wideness</ent>⟦br⟧
